caption: From the moment  you enter this restaurant  the personel give you an agreeable feeling. Very comfortable crew, it is a kind place to to go out with friends and colleagues or with your date. yummy  cooking, specialist  chef, competitive  pay and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
(Translated by Google) fantastic and unique place in a cozy and quality service, super recommended  (Original) fantástico lugar y único en un servicio acogedor y de calidad, super recomendado
Excellent and tasty food, I liked the vibes this spot has, and the employees were welcoming. I will surely visit here next time.

We love Il Mulino at this location, and due to a lack of outdoor seating went next door (same kitchen, can order from same menu) to sit outside at AQ.  Here are the details:  - Definitely sit outside - views overlooking the ocean are a perfect 10 on a breezy night. - The AQ is supposed to be a "Chop House" but really there are very few meat and fish options (1-2 steak options only).  The initial offering is a tasty selection of olives, cheese and bread, but does not compare remotely to the Il Mulino olive oil and parmesan which they were very firmly refusing to bring over from around 100 feet away. Understandable but a shame considering you can order off either menu from the shared kitchen,. - We had the caesar salad (shockingly very small, with a too-citrusy dressing and no anchovies if you seek a legit caesar), the stracciatella soup (served pretty cold), fried calamari (amazingly  tender and tasty with great red sauce, but also served luke cold), for apps. For the main course, had kids butter pasta (way overcooked, but not a big deal), veal parmigiana (superb and vaguely tasted like Uno's pizza - very salty and but also delicious), and past with broccoli rabe and sausage (meh sausage light on flavor, not very hot - maybe luke warm - delicious rich truffle broth, overcooked noodles - overall pretty good).  Our son left hungry... - not a bad meal, a bit less costly than Il Mulino and ambience was amazing. Server was quiet, unengaged, but sort of ok - they like to keep pouring pelligrino to people drinking tap and vice versa - again, not a huge deal but not what we usually enjoy. - get the Spice menu at Il Mulino... skip AQ.  If you want a chop house you picked the wrong place... 25 dollar valet is "reduced" to $20 if you eat there - again, a lot of not-big-deals that added up to a so-so experience.

Worst service, we came today for lunch , sat Wait for 15 minutes, the hostess didn’t explain about the brunch off course was closing in 10 minutes and this was explained by the server how came with attitude. Do you self a favor run away and expend your money somewhere else.. We just stand up and left right there in front of him, the manager didn't even care When we explained the situation. I made reservations on open table it didn’t said nothing about buffet or closing the restaurant. They think they are a fancy place, but the true is the worst of the worst, my recommendation change the staff and update your menus.

Great food, staff was super helpful and everything was fairly priced. The drinks were to die for. Slice of Life is a must have if you visit. Sushi and octopus as well as fish were so good. The view was perfect for a romantic or fun atmosphere.

Worst service, we came yesterday for dinner, sat down and the waiter came gave us the menus and left and never came back, he didn't care. After waiting for 15 min sitting without any attention at all or care for us wanting to order a wine bottle. Also another table beside us stand up and went to speak at the front desk about the terrible service and that the waiter "never came for service". We saw the waiter passing by and call him and told him "Do you care to take our order or what?" (Of course we were mad at that point) he was like "What do you want?". We just stand up and left right there in front of him, the manager didn't even care to call me or see what was going on (I made reservations days before so he had my number), he left right as we were passing in front of the entrance, scare to face the consequences. They think they are a fancy place, pffff the worst of the worst, they think so high of themselves don't have a single integrity hair. Not even the courtesy to call me to apologise. My recommendation, fire the whole management and servers.
Great location...nicest staff... delicious food...and you can have il mulino menu as well

Sushi was excellent.  Nice signature drinks.  Entree ( bone in ribeye ) was good but not great.  Service was excellent.  It was raining out so we had to sit inside but the atmosphere was not as nice as I was expecting.  Had a little bit of a hotel resturant vibe.

Food was pretty good. The outside seating had an incredible view of the beach.

Very casual atmosphere. Service attentive and food was properly prepared and very tasty. Cocktails were a bit pricy. The most unusual thing was the mandatory 18% gratuity that was automatically added to the check, and then taxed.  The server would have done better had they not been so corporate about gratuity.
